dom-xrcubelayer-orientation.name: orientation
dom-xrcubelayer-orientation.summary: The orientation property of the XRCubeLayer interface represents the orientation relative to the space property.
dom-xrcubelayer-orientation.title: XRCubeLayer.orientation

eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.name: redraw_event
eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.summary: The redraw event is sent to the XRCubeLayer object when the underlying resources of the layer are lost or when the XR Compositor can no longer reproject the layer. If this event is sent, authors should redraw the content of the layer in the next XR animation frame.
eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.title: XRCubeLayer: redraw event

eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.name: redraw_event
eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.summary: The redraw event is sent to the XRCylinderLayer object when the underlying resources of the layer are lost or when the XR Compositor can no longer reproject the layer. If this event is sent, authors should redraw the content of the layer in the next XR animation frame.
eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.title: XRCylinderLayer: redraw event

eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.name: redraw_event
eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.summary: The redraw event is sent to the XREquirectLayer object when the underlying resources of the layer are lost or when the XR Compositor can no longer reproject the layer. If this event is sent, authors should redraw the content of the layer in the next XR animation frame.
eventdef-xrlayer-redraw.title: XREquirectLayer: redraw event

dom-xrcubelayer-space.name: space
dom-xrcubelayer-space.summary: The space property of the XRCubeLayer interface represents the layer's spatial relationship with the user's physical environment.
dom-xrcubelayer-space.title: XRCubeLayer.space

xcubelayertype.name: XRCubeLayer
xcubelayertype.summary: The XRCubeLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that renders directly from a cubemap and projects it onto the inside faces of a cube.
xcubelayertype.title: XRCubeLayer

dom-xrcylinderlayer-aspectratio.name: aspectRatio
dom-xrcylinderlayer-aspectratio.summary: The aspectRatio property of the XRCylinderLayer interface represents the ratio of the visible cylinder section. It is the ratio of the width of the visible section of the cylinder divided by its height. The width is calculated by multiplying the radius with the centralAngle.
dom-xrcylinderlayer-aspectratio.title: XRCylinderLayer.aspectRatio

dom-xrcylinderlayer-centralangle.name: centralAngle
dom-xrcylinderlayer-centralangle.summary: The centralAngle property of the XRCylinderLayer interface represents the angle in radians of the visible section of the cylinder.
dom-xrcylinderlayer-centralangle.title: XRCylinderLayer.centralAngle

dom-xrcylinderlayer-radius.name: radius
dom-xrcylinderlayer-radius.summary: The radius property of the XRCylinderLayer interface represents the radius of the cylinder.
dom-xrcylinderlayer-radius.title: XRCylinderLayer.radius

dom-xrcylinderlayer-space.name: space
dom-xrcylinderlayer-space.summary: The space property of the XRCylinderLayer interface represents the layer's spatial relationship with the user's physical environment.
dom-xrcylinderlayer-space.title: XRCylinderLayer.space

dom-xrcylinderlayer-transform.name: transform
dom-xrcylinderlayer-transform.summary: The transform property of the XRCylinderLayer interface represents the offset and orientation relative to the layer's space.
dom-xrcylinderlayer-transform.title: XRCylinderLayer.transform

xrcylinderayertype.name: XRCylinderLayer
xrcylinderayertype.summary: The XRCylinderLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that takes up a curved rectangular space in the virtual environment. Only the front of the layer is visible.
xrcylinderayertype.title: XRCylinderLayer

dom-xrequirectlayer-centralhorizontalang.name: centralHorizontalAngle
dom-xrequirectlayer-centralhorizontalang.summary: The centralHorizontalAngle property of the XREquirectLayer interface represents the central horizontal angle in radians for the sphere.
dom-xrequirectlayer-centralhorizontalang.title: XREquirectLayer.centralHorizontalAngle

dom-xrequirectlayer-lowerverticalangle.name: lowerVerticalAngle
dom-xrequirectlayer-lowerverticalangle.summary: The lowerVerticalAngle property of the XREquirectLayer interface represents the lower vertical angle in radians for the sphere.
dom-xrequirectlayer-lowerverticalangle.title: XREquirectLayer.lowerVerticalAngle

dom-xrequirectlayer-radius.name: radius
dom-xrequirectlayer-radius.summary: The radius property of the XREquirectLayer interface represents the radius of the sphere.
dom-xrequirectlayer-radius.title: XREquirectLayer.radius

dom-xrequirectlayer-space.name: space
dom-xrequirectlayer-space.summary: The space property of the XREquirectLayer interface represents the layer's spatial relationship with the user's physical environment.
dom-xrequirectlayer-space.title: XREquirectLayer.space

dom-xrequirectlayer-transform.name: transform
dom-xrequirectlayer-transform.summary: The transform property of the XREquirectLayer interface represents the offset and orientation relative to the layer's space.
dom-xrequirectlayer-transform.title: XREquirectLayer.transform

dom-xrequirectlayer-upperverticalangle.name: upperVerticalAngle
dom-xrequirectlayer-upperverticalangle.summary: The upperVerticalAngle property of the XREquirectLayer interface represents the upper vertical angle in radians for the sphere.
dom-xrequirectlayer-upperverticalangle.title: XREquirectLayer.upperVerticalAngle

xrequirectlayertype.name: XREquirectLayer
xrequirectlayertype.summary: The XREquirectLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that maps equirectangular coded data onto the inside of a sphere.
xrequirectlayertype.title: XREquirectLayer

dom-xrlayerevent-xrlayerevent.name: XRLayerEvent
dom-xrlayerevent-xrlayerevent.summary: The XRLayerEvent constructor creates and returns a new XRLayerEvent object. These events relate to a change of state of an XRLayer object.
dom-xrlayerevent-xrlayerevent.title: XRLayerEvent()

dom-xrlayerevent-layer.name: layer
dom-xrlayerevent-layer.summary: The layer property of the XRLayerEvent interface is a reference to the XRLayer which generated the event.
dom-xrlayerevent-layer.title: XRLayerEvent.layer

xrlayerevent-interface.name: XRLayerEvent
xrlayerevent-interface.summary: The XRLayerEvent interface of the WebXR Device API is the event type for events related to a change of state of an XRLayer object. These events occur, for example, when the layer needs to be redrawn.
xrlayerevent-interface.title: XRLayerEvent

dom-xrmediabinding-xrmediabinding.name: XRMediaBinding
dom-xrmediabinding-xrmediabinding.summary: The XRMediaBinding() constructor creates and returns a new XRMediaBinding object.
dom-xrmediabinding-xrmediabinding.title: XRMediaBinding()

dom-xrmediabinding-createcylinderlayer.name: createCylinderLayer
dom-xrmediabinding-createcylinderlayer.summary: The createCylinderLayer() method of the XRMediaBinding interface returns an XRCylinderLayer object which is a layer that takes up a curved rectangular space in the virtual environment.
dom-xrmediabinding-createcylinderlayer.title: XRMediaBinding.createCylinderLayer()

dom-xrmediabinding-createequirectlayer.name: createEquirectLayer
dom-xrmediabinding-createequirectlayer.summary: The createEquirectLayer() method of the XRMediaBinding interface returns an XREquirectLayer object which is a layer that maps an equirectangular coded data onto the inside of a sphere.
dom-xrmediabinding-createequirectlayer.title: XRMediaBinding.createEquirectLayer()

dom-xrmediabinding-createquadlayer.name: createQuadLayer
dom-xrmediabinding-createquadlayer.summary: The createQuadLayer() method of the XRMediaBinding interface returns an XRQuadLayer object which is a layer that takes up a flat rectangular space in the virtual environment.
dom-xrmediabinding-createquadlayer.title: XRMediaBinding.createQuadLayer()

XRWebGLBindingtype.name: XRMediaBinding
XRWebGLBindingtype.summary: The XRMediaBinding interface is used to create layers that display the content of an HTMLVideoElement.
XRWebGLBindingtype.title: XRMediaBinding

XRWebGLBindingtype.name: XRWebGLBinding
XRWebGLBindingtype.summary: The XRWebGLBinding interface is used to create layers that have a GPU backend.
XRWebGLBindingtype.title: XRWebGLBinding

dom-xrrenderstate-layers.name: layers
dom-xrrenderstate-layers.summary: The read-only layers property of the XRRenderState interface is an ordered array containing XRLayer objects that are displayed by the XR compositor.
dom-xrrenderstate-layers.title: XRRenderState.layers

dom-xrsubimage-viewport.name: viewport
dom-xrsubimage-viewport.summary: The read-only viewport property of the XRSubImage interface represents the XRViewport that is used when rendering the sub image.
dom-xrsubimage-viewport.title: XRSubImage.viewport

xrsubimagetype.name: XRSubImage
xrsubimagetype.summary: The XRSubImage interface of the WebXR Device API represents what viewport of the GPU texture to use for rendering.
xrsubimagetype.title: XRSubImage

dom-xrwebglbinding-xrwebglbinding.name: XRWebGLBinding
dom-xrwebglbinding-xrwebglbinding.summary: The XRWebGLBinding() constructor creates and returns a new XRWebGLBinding object.
dom-xrwebglbinding-xrwebglbinding.title: XRWebGLBinding()

dom-xrwebglbinding-createcubelayer.name: createCubeLayer
dom-xrwebglbinding-createcubelayer.summary: The createCubeLayer() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns an XRCubeLayer object, which is a layer that renders directly from a cubemap, and projects it onto the inside faces of a cube.
dom-xrwebglbinding-createcubelayer.title: XRWebGLBinding.createCubeLayer()

dom-xrwebglbinding-createcylinderlayer.name: createCylinderLayer
dom-xrwebglbinding-createcylinderlayer.summary: The createCylinderLayer() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns an XRCylinderLayer object, which is a layer that takes up a curved rectangular space in the virtual environment.
dom-xrwebglbinding-createcylinderlayer.title: XRWebGLBinding.createCylinderLayer()

dom-xrwebglbinding-createequirectlayer.name: createEquirectLayer
dom-xrwebglbinding-createequirectlayer.summary: The createEquirectLayer() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns an XREquirectLayer object, which is a layer that maps equirectangular coded data onto the inside of a sphere.
dom-xrwebglbinding-createequirectlayer.title: XRWebGLBinding.createEquirectLayer()

dom-xrwebglbinding-createprojectionlayer.name: createProjectionLayer
dom-xrwebglbinding-createprojectionlayer.summary: The createProjectionLayer() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns an XRProjectionLayer object which is a layer that fills the entire view of the observer and is refreshed close to the device's native frame rate.
dom-xrwebglbinding-createprojectionlayer.title: XRWebGLBinding.createProjectionLayer()

dom-xrwebglbinding-createquadlayer.name: createQuadLayer
dom-xrwebglbinding-createquadlayer.summary: The createQuadLayer() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns an XRQuadLayer object which is a layer that takes up a flat rectangular space in the virtual environment.
dom-xrwebglbinding-createquadlayer.title: XRWebGLBinding.createQuadLayer()

dom-xrwebglbinding-getsubimage.name: getSubImage
dom-xrwebglbinding-getsubimage.summary: The getSubImage() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns a XRWebGLSubImage object representing the WebGL texture to render.
dom-xrwebglbinding-getsubimage.title: XRWebGLBinding.getSubImage()

dom-xrwebglbinding-getviewsubimage.name: getViewSubImage
dom-xrwebglbinding-getviewsubimage.summary: The getViewSubImage() method of the XRWebGLBinding interface returns a XRWebGLSubImage object representing the WebGL texture to render for a view.
dom-xrwebglbinding-getviewsubimage.title: XRWebGLBinding.getViewSubImage()

dom-xrwebglbinding-nativeprojectionscale.name: nativeProjectionScaleFactor
dom-xrwebglbinding-nativeprojectionscale.summary: The read-only nativeProjectionScaleFactor property of the XRWebGLBinding interface represents the scaling factor by which the projection layer's resolution is multiplied by to get the native resolution of the WebXR device's frame buffer.
dom-xrwebglbinding-nativeprojectionscale.title: XRWebGLBinding.nativeProjectionScaleFactor

dom-xrwebglsubimage-colortexture.name: colorTexture
dom-xrwebglsubimage-colortexture.summary: The read-only colorTexture property of the XRWebGLSubImage interface represents the color WebGLTexture object for the XRCompositionLayer to render.
dom-xrwebglsubimage-colortexture.title: XRWebGLSubImage.colorTexture

dom-xrwebglsubimage-depthstenciltexture.name: depthStencilTexture
dom-xrwebglsubimage-depthstenciltexture.summary: The read-only depthStencilTexture property of the XRWebGLSubImage interface represents the depth/stencil WebGLTexture object for the XRCompositionLayer to render.
dom-xrwebglsubimage-depthstenciltexture.title: XRWebGLSubImage.depthStencilTexture

dom-xrwebglsubimage-imageindex.name: imageIndex
dom-xrwebglsubimage-imageindex.summary: The read-only imageIndex property of the XRWebGLSubImage interface is a number representing the offset into the texture array if the layer was requested with texture-array; null otherwise.
dom-xrwebglsubimage-imageindex.title: XRWebGLSubImage.imageIndex

dom-xrwebglsubimage-textureheight.name: textureHeight
dom-xrwebglsubimage-textureheight.summary: The read-only textureHeight property of the XRWebGLSubImage interface is a number representing the height in pixels of the GL attachment.
dom-xrwebglsubimage-textureheight.title: XRWebGLSubImage.textureHeight

dom-xrwebglsubimage-texturewidth.name: textureWidth
dom-xrwebglsubimage-texturewidth.summary: The read-only textureWidth property of the XRWebGLSubImage interface is a number representing the width in pixels of the GL attachment.
dom-xrwebglsubimage-texturewidth.title: XRWebGLSubImage.textureWidth

xrwebglsubimagetype.name: XRWebGLSubImage
xrwebglsubimagetype.summary: The XRWebGLSubImage interface is used during rendering of WebGL layers.
xrwebglsubimagetype.title: XRWebGLSubImage
